body:
Ok here is a minimal test which demonstrates the issue.

When run with a 2GB max heap size, this test passes on Junit 5.2, but hits OutOfMemoryError on Junit 5.3.  And I find that unacceptable... never before has any version of Junit so heavily punished test classes which store large amounts of data.
```java
import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;

/**
 * Demonstrates the Junit 5.3 memory leak issue discussed at:
 *   https://github.com/junit-team/junit5/issues/1578
 * Intended to be run using a 2 GB max heap size.
 */
class Junit53MemoryLeakDemoTest {
    private final byte[] gigabyte = new byte[1073741824];

    @Test void test1() { }
    @Test void test2() { }
    @Test void test3() { }
}
```
